<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - FRONT DRIVE AXLE: SPICER S-9000 - WHEEL END DISASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="6">
        <title>WHEEL END DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>International does not offer asbestos lining. The long term effects of non-asbestos fibers have
                    not been determined. Therefore, the following information is important when handling these
                    materials.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <para>The Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) of the United States Department of Labor has set
            the maximum allowable exposure level for airborne asbestos at 0.2 fibers of asbestos per cubic centimeter of
            air (0.2f/cc) as an eight hour timed weighted average. This guideline should also be followed for
            non-asbestos fibers. It is recommended that workers doing brake work should take steps to minimize exposure
            to airborne brake lining particles. OSHA APPROVED RESPIRATORS SHOULD BE WORN AT ALL TIMES DURING BRAKE
            SERVICING.
        </para>
        <para>Proper procedures to reduce exposure include segregation of areas where brake work is done, use of
            enclosed cells with filtered vacuums and/or a well ventilated area.
        </para>
        <para>COMPRESSED AIR OR DRY BRUSHING SHOULD NEVER BE USED FOR CLEANING BRAKE ASSEMBLIES.</para>
        <para>Workers should wash before eating, drinking or smoking, should shower after working and should never wear
            work clothes home. Work clothes should be vacuumed and laundered without shaking.
        </para>
        <para>Use
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0200965">Figure 65</hotlnk>
            as a reference to disassemble the wheel end.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0200965" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0200965" filename="../figg02/G0200965.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 65. Wheel End Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Oil Seal</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Spindle Bushing</callout1>
                <callout1>3. Spindle</callout1>
                <callout1>4. Air Chamber Assembly</callout1>
                <callout1>5. Brake Assembly (Left Side Shown)</callout1>
                <callout1>6. Oil Seal</callout1>
                <callout1>7. Bearing Cone</callout1>
                <callout1>8. Hex Bolt</callout1>
                <callout1>9. Flat Washer</callout1>
                <callout1>10. Drum-Cast Wheel End</callout1>
                <callout1>11. Bearing Cup</callout1>
                <callout1>12. Cast Wheel End</callout1>
                <callout1>13. Stud</callout1>
                <callout1>14. Stud</callout1>
                <callout1>15. Bearing Cup</callout1>
                <callout1>16. Bearing Cone</callout1>
                <callout1>17. Keyed Washer</callout1>
                <callout1>18. Wheel Bearing Nut</callout1>
                <callout1>19. Lockwasher</callout1>
                <callout1>20. Shim</callout1>
                <callout1>21. Spindle Flange</callout1>
                <callout1>22. Socket Head Screw</callout1>
                <callout1>23. Nut-Lock</callout1>
                <callout1>24. Stud, L.H. Thread</callout1>
                <callout1>25. Drum Disc Wheel End</callout1>
                <callout1>26. Disc Wheel End</callout1>
                <callout1>27. Hex Nut</callout1>
                <callout1>28. Flat Washer</callout1>
                <callout1>29. Hex Nut</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove socket head capscrew from center of drive flange (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200966">Figure 66</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200966" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200966" filename="../figg02/G0200966.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 66. Remove Capscrew</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove drive flange lock nuts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200967">Figure 67</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200967" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200967" filename="../figg02/G0200967.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Remove Flange Lock Nuts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread in two 3/8-16 bolts to remove drive flange.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove drive flange shims. Save shims for possible reuse during reassembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Straighten bent tabs of wheel end lockwasher (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200968">Figure 68</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200968" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200968" filename="../figg02/G0200968.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 68. Straighten Bent Tabs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove outer wheel bearing nut, tabbed lockwasher and inner wheel bearing nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove hub and drum assembly, including bearing, thrust washer and wheel bearings.</para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Carefully remove the hub and drum assembly to prevent dropping the outer bearing.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove brake drum dust shield (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200969">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200969" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200969" filename="../figg02/G0200969.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 69. Remove Dust Shield</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove spindle mounting lock nuts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove brake assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove spindle from knuckle assembly carefully so as not to damage the spindle bushing and
                outer shaft oil seal which are pressed into the spindle bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200970">Figure 70</hotlnk>). Replace any worn or damaged parts.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200970" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200970" filename="../figg02/G0200970.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 70. Remove Spindle</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
